<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-09T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-09T10:00:00-05:00" n="1032" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1032">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">662.6731/147: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-09T17:00:00+02:00">October 9, 1941—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 10—12:24 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>377. The German-Turkish commercial agreement was signed about noon
                                    today.<note n="46" xml:id="d1032fn46">For text, see <hi rend="italic">Reichsgesetzblatt</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, No. 2, November 15, 1941, p.
                                    375.</note></p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>